      {
        "content": "Social media platforms need reform to safeguard mental health due to the pervasive issue of cyberbullying. The anonymity and widespread reach of social media amplify bullying, making it relentless and inescapable for victims. This constant exposure can lead to severe anxiety, depression, and in extreme cases, suicidal ideation. Current mechanisms for reporting and managing such abuse are inadequate, often failing to provide timely and effective support. Reforming these platforms by implementing stronger protective measures and proactive monitoring can significantly reduce harm, creating a safer environment for users and promoting healthier online interactions.",
