      {
        "content": "Social media platforms have become notorious for violating privacy rights, often exploiting user data for profit without adequate consent or transparency. These platforms track and analyze user behavior, creating detailed profiles that are sold to advertisers, which not only infringes on individual privacy but also raises concerns about data security and manipulation. The lack of stringent regulations allows these practices to continue unchecked, putting personal information at risk of breaches and misuse. Protecting privacy in the digital age requires robust reforms, ensuring that users have control over their data and are informed about how it is being used and shared.",
